---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
---
<Layout title="About this page">
	<Navbar></Navbar>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 mt-12 flex flex-wrap">
        <div class="max-w-screen-md mb-8 lg:mb-16">
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-4xl tracking-tight font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">About</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-500 sm:text-xl dark:text-gray-400">There's a couple of shops of electronic components 
                that I like to follow  but searching through those sites its a bit messy and inconvinient. So I started
                gathering their product data (gently, every couple of days) and put it in a table. This page is my way to 
                display that table. It's inspired in rpilocator.com  
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-row justify-center items-center mx-auto gap-4 md:gap-8"> 
            <svg class="w-[48px] h-[48px] text-gray-800 dark:text-white" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 16 20">
